fr.cnrs.iees.properties

Interface ExtendablePropertyList

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, fr.ens.biologie.generic.DataContainer, PropertyListGetters, PropertyListSetters, ReadOnlyPropertyList, ResizeablePropertyList, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sealable, SimplePropertyList, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sizeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ExtendablePropertyListImpl

    public interface ExtendablePropertyList
extends SimplePropertyList, ResizeablePropertyList, fr.ens.biologie.generic.Sealable

    A mutable SimplePropertyList, i.e. which can grow and shrink.

    1. Mutable, i.e. the list of properties can grow and shrink.
    2. Default properties: none.

    The contract is as follows: add...() methods will add a new property to the list while set...() methods will only set a value for an existing property. They should return an error if the property does not exist.

    Instances of this class are Sealable, i.e. they can be made immutable after some time by calling seal(). This enables, for example, to read properties from a file without knowing how many are expected, and then make the PropertyList immutable after the file has been closed.

    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 29-8-2017
